{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769629660,"nonce":"JAdhw5XwCL9UvEDdj6EukoVRJLI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mf0eu","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/107","origin":"github"},"title":"Add model parameter to set_git_identity_env.sh for complete AI signatures","message":"## Problem\nWhen AI agents use `set_git_identity_env.sh`, the script shows \"Model: Unknown Model\" because it doesn't accept a model name parameter. This leads to incomplete signatures in commits and GitHub issues.\n\n## Example\n```bash\nsource .agent/scripts/set_git_identity_env.sh \"Copilot CLI Agent\" \"roland+copilot-cli@ccom.unh.edu\"\n# Output: Model: Unknown Model\n```\n\nAgents then have to manually add model info to signatures, leading to inconsistent formatting.\n\n## Proposed Solution\nUpdate `set_git_identity_env.sh` to accept optional 3rd parameter for model name:\n\n```bash\nsource .agent/scripts/set_git_identity_env.sh \"Copilot CLI Agent\" \"roland+copilot-cli@ccom.unh.edu\" \"Claude Sonnet 4.5\"\n```\n\nScript should:\n- Accept model as 3rd parameter (optional for backward compatibility)\n- Set `AGENT_MODEL` environment variable\n- Display model in confirmation output\n- Update `AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md` with example usage\n\n## Impact\n- ✅ Consistent AI signatures across commits and issues\n- ✅ Clear attribution showing which model did the work\n- ✅ Easier for humans to understand agent capabilities\n- ✅ Better tracking of which models are effective at tasks\n\n## Priority\n🔴 High - Affects all AI agent work and signature quality\n\n## Session Evidence\nSession: 66b4eea3-8aff-4a81-88b6-6aafd77a65e3\n- User asked me to add model to signatures when creating sub-issues\n- Script output showed \"Unknown Model\" \n- Manual workaround required for each signature\n\n---\n**🤖 Reported-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}